You would recall that the acting Managing Director of the Niger Delta Development Company (NDDC) Prof. Kemebradikumo Pondei and his team on Thursday, walked out on legislators investigating the alleged N40 billion irregular expenditure in the commission. Pondei stormed out of the hearing on Thursday in Abuja, after accusing the Chairman of the committee Rep. Olubumi Tunji-Ojo (APC-Ondo) of corruption. However, Pondei returned to the National Assembly on Monday for the investigation to be continued. See photos below: <img class="wp-image-1427583 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0842d04f-d6a4-40ba-be64-cd6f0378b10c.jpg?resize=640%2C480&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0842d04f-d6a4-40ba-be64-cd6f0378b10c.jpg?w=1040&amp;ssl=1 1040w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0842d04f-d6a4-40ba-be64-cd6f0378b10c.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0842d04f-d6a4-40ba-be64-cd6f0378b10c.jpg?resize=1024%2C768&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0842d04f-d6a4-40ba-be64-cd6f0378b10c.jpg?resize=768%2C576&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0842d04f-d6a4-40ba-be64-cd6f0378b10c.jpg?resize=58%2C44&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0842d04f-d6a4-40ba-be64-cd6f0378b10c.jpg?resize=260%2C194&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0842d04f-d6a4-40ba-be64-cd6f0378b10c.jpg?resize=173%2C130&amp;ssl=1 173w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> By Tordue Salem - Abuja The Acting Managing Director of Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC), Kemebradikumo Daniel Pondei and his staff staged a walk-out on the House of Representatives Committee on NDDC on Thursday. The drama